      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental validation test conditions must span the full COU operating envelope of 5 flow-speed combinations; blood analogue fluid properties documented with uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used porcine blood at three of the five required operating points. The two highest-speed conditions were not experimentally tested. Fluid property uncertainty bounds were reported only for viscosity, not for the hemolysis sensitivity coefficient. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative agreement metric (e.g., E% or U95 band) applied to hemolysis index at all COU operating points; simulation uncertainty intervals must overlap experimental uncertainty intervals.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison was performed at three tested operating points; simulation U95 intervals do not overlap experimental intervals at two of those points. The two untested operating points have no output comparison at all. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The hemolysis index QoI used in validation must be the same scalar quantity used in the clinical acceptance criterion; no proxy metrics permitted at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Validation used a normalized hemolysis index (NIH) while the clinical acceptance criterion references plasma free hemoglobin (pfHb) concentration. A documented mapping between NIH and pfHb exists in literature but has not been formally justified within this assessment. Achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    },
